{
  "stem": "15686.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My father was-- and this is absolutely typical for that period in time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, it was like that at my friend's house and everyone's house-- the man, the breadwinner, was sacrosanct.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was on a pedestal and, you know, his word was law.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first things that affected me was probably the transferring school in elementary school, when I had to go to an all-Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They simply told me-- my parents told me-- well, a new law has come out, and you can't go to this school anymore.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when the school year ends, you'll be going to another school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And instead of walking maybe five or six blocks to school, I now had to walk for about, oh, 40 minutes or so to get to the school-- this Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this Jewish school was a converted apartment building surrounded by other apartment buildings in which Gentile people lived.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they didn't like the fact at all that there was a Jewish school among them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they made life very difficult, aside from the Hitler Youth waiting for us when we came out and beating us up and harassing the girls, in particular.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And German education demanded that boys and girls go to separate classes, but the school was there for both.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But for instance, during recess, the neighbors in the other adjacent apartment buildings had complained that there was too much noise during recess.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Children who are in class for three hours, after they're released for a half an hour, they get a little wild.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we used to run around and scream a little bit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the school authorities decreed that we had to walk two by two in a large circle through the school yard.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were not allowed to talk.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
